The ABC7 Vaccine Tracker shows that about 5.2 million people across New Jersey are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 as of Aug. 8. About 6 million people statewide have received at least one dose.

Statewide, ABC7’s analysis shows the number of people fully vaccinated is about 59% of all New Jersey residents.

The data shows the share of New Jersey residents 12 or over who are now fully vaccinated is about 68.8%. In May, the federal government approved the first vaccines for people ages 12-15, but it remains unavailable to children under 12.

You can search every vaccine provider with shots available today in New Jersey in our searchable map below.

How is New Jersey doing getting everyone vaccinated?

The pace of vaccinations has slowed. Over the last seven days, the data shows an average of 7,559 people per day became fully vaccinated, compared to 9,738 people per day the seven days before that. That’s a change of -22.4%.

You can see the percentage of all people vaccinated day-by-day in the chart below.

The CDC data is updated daily, but the agency says its total number of vaccinations could be behind actual doses administered by up to 72 hours based on when it receives data from state and local health departments.

What’s happening in my New Jersey county?

You can look up the progress thus far in every New Jersey county below. Start typing your county name in the search bar to find it faster. These county totals, from the CDC, include doses from state and federal government providers and only include the county’s residents.

If I am eligible, where can I get vaccinated?

At least 1,362 pharmacies, medical facilities and other providers have vaccines in stock across New Jersey. You can search all of them in our live map, which pulls data every morning from the VaccineFinder system at the CDC’s vaccines.gov.

The yellow and green circles show clusters of locations. If you click them, the map will zoom in to show individual locations. Clicking a red marker will show the vaccine location’s name, address and ways to get more information online or by phone.

You can use the search button at top right to zoom to your address or zip code.
